Five  former senior Transnet executives have been arrested for allegedly contravening the Public Finance Management Act, fraud, corruption and money laundering. The Investigating Directorate said the five would appear  in the Palm Ridge magistrate’s court sitting as the specialised commercial crimes court on Friday. “The arrests took place  at about 7am this morning [Friday] at  Brackendowns police station,” said Investigating Directorate national spokesperson Sindisiwe Seboka. TimesLIVE